{
  "stem": "27335.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And somehow, uh, the family on my mother's side found out, and there was a young boy-- the youngest boy in the family-- he became an apprentice to my father.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he got to know my mother, and they got married.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then, and then the first product became, that was me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Kemesce-- that was the name.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, these names are very hard to pronounce in English, or-- or in Hebrew, or anybody else.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Hungarians are a very peculiar, complicated name.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was Szabolcs, it's in [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Szabolcs is in the northeast part of Hungary.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There is only one-- only one province, or one or two provinces between-- between Hungary and the present day Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And at that time it was Poland and Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was-- there was no Ukraine, matter of fact, at that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the village was a very large and a peculiar village.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All the wanderers in the county, many, many foreigners settled down-- like- like my father-- because the Hungarians themselves, very-- well, shall I use this term?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Backwater, in a sense, these tradesmen and-- and merchants, and so on.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And many of the merchants-- most of them, most of them-- Jewish people, you see?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Most of the merchants, and some-- some tradesmen, like the tin smith, and barber, and so on.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, uh, among this, they used to call them the-- the aliens, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So my father was one of them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was a Jewish blacksmith, and another one a Slovak this, and then a German that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's how they-- the trade, and the trade and commerce came about in that religion.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It, uh, it became a real-- a real highly-- highly commercialized and so on.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
